codex
The strongest integrity issue so far is in version cloning: the clone SQL predates several formulation columns, so a “new version from current” silently drops process overhead and ingredient-level WIP/substitute mappings. I’m checking deletion cascades and refresh behavior now, and I’ll distinguish confirmed defects from areas that are merely implementation choices.
